  "title": "Crystal Ball",
  "summaries": [
    "The <b>Crystal Ball</b> is a <linked>furniture</linked> item which functions as a <linked>crafting station</linked>. Placing and pressing <span class=\"key\"><linked>⚷ Open / Activate</linked></span> on it grants the <b>Clairvoyance</b> <linked>buff</linked>. It is purchased from the <linked>Wizard</linked> for <span class=\"coin\" title=\"10 Gold Coins\" data-sort-value=\"100000\"><span class=\"gc\">10<i> GC</i></span></span>.",
    "The Clairvoyance buff boosts the following magic-related stats:",
    "<ul><li>+20 maximum <linked>mana</linked></li><li>+5% magic damage</li><li>+2% magic <linked>critical strike chance</linked></li><li>−2% mana usage</li></ul>",
    "On the <linked>[img:Desktop version]</linked><linked> Desktop version</linked>, <linked>[img:Console version]</linked><linked> Console version</linked>, and <linked>[img:Mobile version]</linked><linked> Mobile version</linked>, the Clairvoyance buff lasts until the player <linked>dies</linked> or leaves the world. On the <linked>[img:Old-gen console version]</linked><linked> Old-gen console version</linked> and <linked>Nintendo 3DS</linked><linked>[img:Nintendo 3DS version]</linked><linked> version</linked>, it lasts for 10 minutes. On all versions, the buff can be canceled at any time  by right-clicking the icon (<linked>[img:Desktop version]</linked>),  by selecting the icon using Cycle Next/Previous Buff and then pressing Remove Buff (<linked>[img:Console version]</linked>),  by selecting the icon and canceling it in the equipment menu (<linked>[img:Old-gen console version]</linked>),  by double-tapping the buff icon (<linked>[img:Mobile version]</linked>), or  by canceling the buff from the buffs screen (<linked>[img:Nintendo 3DS version]</linked>).",
    "Unlike <linked>equipment buff items</linked>, the Crystal Ball must be placed in order to activate the buff. It can be mined with a <linked>pickaxe</linked> or <linked>drill</linked> and picked up again, even while the buff is active, which will not cancel the buff. Placement is only dependent on an adequate space of 2×2 tiles being available."
  ],
